doc.after: On 27Â December 2009, the German Wikipedia edition exceeded 1,000,000 articles,[7] becoming the first edition after the English-language Wikipedia to do so. The millionth article was Ernie Wasson. In November 2008, 90% of the edition's articles had more than 512 bytes, 49% had more than 2 kilobytes, and the average article size was 3,476 bytes.[8] In the middle of 2009 this edition had nearly 250,000 biographies and in December 2006 more than 48,500 disambiguations.[9]
